# boilerX rules

This is an npm workspaces monorepo with packages `@boilerx/{shared,evolve,templates,cli}`.

## Mandatory before editing

- Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`. It is the source of truth.
- TypeScript strict mode; respect `noUncheckedIndexedAccess` and `verbatimModuleSyntax`.
- ESM imports inside the repo MUST end in `.js` (NodeNext resolution).
- Cross-package imports use `@boilerx/<pkg>`, never relative paths.

## Style

- Files: `kebab-case.ts`. Types: `PascalCase`. Variables/functions: `camelCase`.
- No `any`. Prefer `unknown` + narrowing.
- No narrative comments. Comments only for non-obvious *why*.
- Logs via `createLogger` from `@boilerx/shared`. Human CLI output via `picocolors`.

## Capa 2 (`packages/evolve`) sacred invariants

- The `Judge` is immutable during a run. Its prompt and code are hash-pinned.
- Workers may NEVER write outside their `hypothesis.affectedFiles`.
- Workers may NEVER touch `.judge/`, `.evolve/`, `tests/judge/`, or `Makefile`.
- Architects and Judges are READ-ONLY over the codebase.

## Commits

Conventional Commits:
- `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor(scope):`, `test(scope):`.
- One concern per PR. Split if touching Capa 1 and Capa 2 simultaneously.

## When unsure

Stop and ask in chat. Do not guess.
